.TH man 1 "25 Nov 2020" "0.1" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- Simple shell made in C to interact with a linux operating system.

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <string.h>

#include <stdio.h>

#include <stdlib.h>

#include <unistd.h>

#include <sys/types.h>

#include <sys/stat.h>

#include <unistd.h>

#include <sys/wait.h>

#include <limits.h>

#include <signal.h>

.SH DESCRIPTION
This simple shell will works same as shell. It means that  the program will
 receive keyboard commands and passes them to the operating system to carry out.

.SH Return Value
Return status value when user want to exit the shell.

.SH PATH

It will look inside al directions in PATH env variable for executable.

.SH COMMANDS
.B ls [OPTION] : list directory contents

.B pwd : print name of current/working directory

.B Handling Ctrl+C:
The simple shell will be terminated.

.B Handling Ctrl+D:
The simple shell will be terminated.

.SH BUILINTS
.B exit [STATUS] : cause normal process termination.

.B env : run a program in a modified environment.

.B cd [PATH]: change directory

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
Command options will be typed after the main command followed by a space and a
 '-' symbol.

.SH EXAMPLE

[command] [options]

$ ls -l


.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

.SH AUTHOR
Chloe Dumit, Julian Arbini.
